**Source -**
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1QbUZH105H4Rq7Uu5L0cbkTqLp4tbJj17?usp=sharing


Step1: Mount Google drive to the Google collab notebook.
>Press on the drive button in the files tab on the left side of the screen or run the first block of code.
>Authorize Drive.


Step2: Add Datasets folder "input" to drive.
>The source leads to a folder named input, containing the two dataset folders.
>Click on the three dots on top right corner.
>Select Organize.
>Add Shortcut.
>Select Collab Notebook folder.
>Press Add.


There are two datasets inside the input folder:
tmdb-movie-metadata: Metadata on ~5,000 movies from TMDb (43.6MB)
the-movies-dataset: Metadata on over 45,000 movies. 26 million ratings from over 270,000 users.(900MB)
